# SVG processing guidelines

- Never redraw or hand‑convert SVGs; use the source files exactly as supplied.
- Inline every SVG at build‑time:

  - Read the raw `<svg>` markup from its source URL (often `http://localhost:*/…/*.svg`).
  - Paste that markup directly into the component’s JSX; do not ship an external `<img>` tag or a runtime fetch.

- Optimise before inlining — run the markup through [SVGO] to strip comments, fill, stroke, and width / height attributes that can be driven by CSS.

- Let the component control dimensions with CSS unless the design shows fixed pixel sizes.
- Remove hard‑coded fill colours so the SVG can inherit currentColor.

- ID collisions: prefix any internal IDs / clipPaths with the component name `(id="TooltipArrow")`, or add `prefixIds: true` in the SVGO step.
- For decorative icons, set `aria-hidden="true"` and `focusable="false"`.

- Re‑use: if an identical icon appears in other components, promote it to `src/components/Icon.tsx` and import it as` <Icon glyph={glyphName} />`.
